# User documentation maintenance

The in-app user guide is rendered from a single source file and served at **`GET /docs`**.

| Item | Location |
|------|----------|
| **Source (edit this)** | [`src/main/resources/documentation/USER_GUIDE.md`](../../src/main/resources/documentation/USER_GUIDE.md) |
| Renderer | `UserDocumentationService` (CommonMark → HTML) |
| Page template | [`src/main/resources/templates/docs.html`](../../src/main/resources/templates/docs.html) |
| Styles | [`src/main/resources/META-INF/resources/css/docs.css`](../../src/main/resources/META-INF/resources/css/docs.css) |
| Entry point | Help → **About Video Creator** (`help-about` → opens `/docs` in a new tab) |

## When to update (same task / PR)

Update `USER_GUIDE.md` whenever you add, remove, or materially change **user-visible** behavior, including:

- Menu items, toolbar buttons, keyboard shortcuts
- Timeline, preview, export, or media-library workflows
- Status bar messages or progress indicators
- New or changed REST endpoints consumed by the UI
- Requirements (MLT, MongoDB, supported formats)

Also update in the **same change**:

1. [`docs/INTERFACE_FEATURES.md`](../../docs/INTERFACE_FEATURES.md) — feature checklist status
2. [`docs/UI_ELEMENTS.md`](../../docs/UI_ELEMENTS.md) — if UI elements were added or renamed (see `ui-elements-catalog.mdc`)

## Required edits in USER_GUIDE.md

1. Describe the feature in the correct section (or add a section).
2. Include **how to access** it (menu path, button, shortcut).
3. Bump the **`Last updated:`** line at the top (ISO date: `YYYY-MM-DD`).
4. Keep tables and lists accurate — remove deleted features.

## Do not

- Edit rendered HTML in `docs.html` for prose (layout only).
- Ship user-facing features without documenting them in `USER_GUIDE.md`.
- Duplicate long prose in README; link to `/docs` instead.

## Verify

1. `./mvnw quarkus:dev` → open `/docs` and confirm the new text appears.
2. Editor → **Help → About Video Creator** opens the same page in a new tab.

